<br>
Tonight was sort of a long string of bad luck, but we'll get her next time.  The first time I led a Vox raid for CoG we were under the gun with a single fail behind us... we beat the snot out of her that time, we'll do it again.<br>
<br>
I'll post a better write-up tomorrow.  In the mean time, thanks to everyone who came, especially those who stayed until the very end.<br>
<br>
And a very special thanks goes out to Steelheart and his Harbinger CR team who came in to bail us out - as well as Marley who brought his epic to make the res'ing go so much faster than we could have done without him.<br>
<br>
====&gt;[ New and improved write-up ]&lt;===<br>
<br>
Well, given the number of signups, I expected to have a very full raid, and expected to have to turn a number of people away.  As it turned out a lot of the sign-ups didn't show (this is alarmingly usual on CoG raids) and we ended up heading in with around 57 people, all told.  9 mostly full combat groups, and 2 (later 3 when Steelheart arrived, and thank Marr he did...) 53+ support folks.<br>
<br>
Groups starting zoning in and clearing the way to the king room at a decent hour.  I arrived just in time for someone to pull the Diplomat, who, as usual, lasted about 3 steps through the door before falling over.  What a level 34 Ice Giant is doing at ground zero for a large target raid zone, I couldn't tell ya... being a spellcaster doesn't do you much good when you don't last long enough to cast a single spell regardless of being interrupted or not.<br>
<br>
Kefo and Danaldil began to pull the IG's after a bit of admin talk - I hadn't assigned MA and SA until we were inside, nor told anyone who the rads loot master (mistress?) was.  The pre-lair clearing went pretty smoothly.<br>
<br>
The lair pull itself was a little chaotic, but it usually is... it's not easy to seperate out the 4 giants and the 2+ terrors and occasional spider that tend to come out of there.  At the end it seemed like different groups were all fighting different mobs, but everything turned out ok in the end - all mobs dead, and only a few casualties in our ranks.  Pretty typical as lair pulls go, really.<br>
<br>
The buffing for Vox was a little problematic - both of our Shaman buffers had to leave early, so a number of the casters, as well as the bulk of the buff-line itself missed those stat buffs.  But all the melee classes got a full round of buffs, and ultimately, they're the one's that really need those.<br>
<br>
Wally, Zorokk, Abreanna, Findiar, and Biaxident handled the occasionaly link-death or mana short issue with remarkable ease - and thanks to everyone else who helped out in there - I'm not sure how Troubadore managed to conjur up a mage to hand out some much needed mod rods, but I'm thankful he managed it.  Speaking of Troubadore... I never did do a full write-up of the last raid, but he deserves mention forgiving up the RBB that he had by all rights won and allowing a re-roll to make sure that it went to a melee class - his action captures the true spirit of the &quot;Need before Greed&quot; loot policy that CoG tries to follow.<br>
<br>
A special thanks to Lainiea for coming along and providing us with the much needed Circle of Summer buff, as we had no level 52 Druids in the combat parties to provide it, and without that buff... well, we would have died even sooner. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
There was a lot of random chatter in the chat-room when we were going over strategy... not so much in the beginning, but quite a lot at the end.  While this tends to happen a lot on CoG raids, something that everyone should understand is that anyone chattering during those strategy sessions can make people who may not already &quot;know everything&quot; miss important information.<br>
<br>
The charge against Vox went pretty much as normal... except that she didn't seem to be taking much damage, and seemed to be dishing out a hell of a lot in return.  It took a very long time for us to get her down to the range where we normally send in casters.  I should probably have sent in casters earlier to make up for the fact that tanks were dropping faster than normal, but I won't dwell on the &quot;could-have-done's&quot; of the night.<br>
<br>
I did, however, get an alarming number of reports of tanks not being healed, and healers not running in to die when out of mana.  I can't stress how important that is.  If the tanks die, we lose.  Period.  Casters may do a hell of a lot more damage, but that cannot get in to cast if there are no tanks higher on Vox' hate list.  Likewise, if constant pressure is not kept up, all monsters go into a sort of &quot;super-regen&quot; mode.  When there is nothing on Vox' hate list, she regens well over 1000hp/tick - no casters can keep up with that.<br>
<br>
As for there being too much overlap in healing... that particular &quot;heal anyone that comes in&quot; strategy has done us very well for a very long time.  Yes, there is some mana wastage... but having the tanks healed as fast as possible is more than worth the cost of a little healing overlap.<br>
<br>
Now, please don't get me wrong here - I am NOT saying that we failed because the healers didn't do their jobs - that is not the case at all.<br>
<br>
We failed because Vox didn't want to die last night.  The spells she chooses to use are totally random.  Usually it's a mixture of small heals, fear, DD, and dispells.  Last night she seemed hell bent on casting almost nothing but DD's and dispells.  My own buffs were blown away very early on (usually I have at least 1 or 2 left at the end), and she was casting her cold DD with alarming regularity.  I normally resist most of that, taking 50-150hp damage per cast as long as my CR holds up... last night I was regularly taking 400+ (max damage from that effect is around 500 or so).<br>
<br>
With that combination of spells being cast, tanks were going back for heals a lot more often, and dying a lot faster... and as was shown last night, that's bad news for a raid against Vox.<br>
<br>
In our previous win, she actually got off a Complete Heal when she was at about 60% life, but we didn't break a stride and just pounded her back down again... this time we weren't so lucky.<br>
<br>
So... after the tanks were pretty much all dead, I told Abreanna to throw in the towel.  As Kellory pointed out, I should have made my choice of secondary battle-commander clearer.  I asked her if she was willing to do it, and when she said yes I promptly forgot to tell everyone else in the chat-room... bad Paladin, no biscuit.<br>
<br>
CR was started almost immediatly by Steelheart.  I wasn't there, having died when she was still at the 'V' in Vox... so I'm not sure just where the communication foul-up was made... but EVERYONE should have consented Steelheart by the time he got to your body.  In future I will probably make it a standing order for everyone to /consent whoever is going to be our CR rogue(s) as soon as they die.  Granted, that's a lot easier when Vox dies and we don't have to worry about retrieval for anything other than the pit deaths... but oh well.<br>
<br>
After Steelheart had gotten all of the readily available bodies out of the lair, as well as all the bodies out of the pits, we had to move Vox for him to get the last corpses out from under her.  As I've done a few times before, I went into the lair, and as soon as I saw her moving towards me, I ran like hell.  Now, normally what happens here is that she will follow me to the doorway into her lair... spit curses and question my genetic heratige for a while... and then start pacing angrily in her lair.  I have seen her poke her head out into the triage area a number of times before, and that's usually as fast as she goes.<br>
<br>
So I ran when I saw her agro on me... get down into the buffing hall, start to turn around, and Vox pops up on top of me, claws me to death in short order, and proceeds to kill everyone there...  I typed &quot;/say oh shit&quot; as I was dying... I'm not sure if hitting return to actually say that got thorugh or not... heh.<br>
<br>
If that ever has to happen again... hell... maybe I'll have everyone camp out before we try that... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
From there on out CR turned ugly.  Ice Giants started to repopulate all over the place, multilple people got trapped into death-loops at bind points...  bad mojo, friends.<br>
<br>
After Steelheart died fighting a giant, a Harbingers team was called in to save our bacon.  Shortly after they arrived and began dispatching the repop'd giants, I sent my druid out to fetch Marley, and epic wielding cleric of Grey Hawke, who came in and helped out immensly with the res'ing the appaling number of bodies littering the halls.<br>
<br>
Now, I wasn't there when most of this was going on... but one thing I will say is, in a bad situation like that, the worst possible action is to panic.  If you are in a death-loop, hit &quot;/q&quot; - this will disconnect you.  Log back in as an alternate character and give your group leader, or the raid leader a tell and let them know who you are.<br>
<br>
Also, I know it's hard to sit there not knowing what's going on... but please... I can only type so fast, and with everyone asking me for updates every couple of minutes in the middle of me trying to find out what's going on and or coordinate CR efforts... I get worn out pretty fast.  Apologies to those people I snapped at, but hopefully you understand where I was coming from at that point.<br>
<br>
CR efforts finally ended around 2:30am PST... almost 10 hours after the raid had started officially...  A successful Vox raid normally takes somewhere in the 6-8 hour range, at least... but there really isn't the same weariness after a success.<br>
<br>
I'd like to thank once more all the people who stayed until the very end.  When it gets that late, I really can't blame anyone who needs to leave early... but there's always a special feeling between everyone still there when the job is finally done.<br>
<br>
I know of two people who still had bodies left behind when we left... they were offline at the time...  if either of you still need to have your bodies recovered, give me a tell in game and I'll try and dig up a CR team to go in and kill the giants in the way.  Unfortunately I have family obligations for most of the next few days, and then a PoF raid on Sunday... so I don't know how available I'll be. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
In the end, yes, we did fail... but we also put in a hell of an effort, and we'll get her next time for sure.  Vox is a tough cookie, and a single loss against her is almost to be expected these days.  Of all the guilds and alliances on the Vox and Nagefen rotations, FoF/CoG has one of the best records against them, especially against Vox, of recent times - and I expect us to continue chalking up marks in the &quot;W&quot; column with regularity in the future! <p>-Kommisar Nils "Can-Head" Hansen -- Guild Officer. Master Smith. Tank.
