<br>
The heroes of the night were without a doubt Steelheart and the Harbringers that came to our rescue.  I am so thankful that you guys came and helped.  You efforts are so appreciated.  And I know that everyone shares that sentiment. <br>
<br>
Also, I personally want to thank Senadwen from Paralax and his guildmate that came to assist with rezzes <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    As always you guys are just wonderful.<br>
<br>
I know that everyone is disappointed in the raid.  I was personally horrified to be knee deep in my own corpses, but a failure is truly for people that do not try.  <br>
<br>
We came, we organized, we united, and we all fought and died with much honor. Vox was just uncooperative.  She was down to less than 20% health and that in itself is a big accomplishment. <br>
<br>
A special thanks to the members of the raid that stayed until the end and tried to keep morale up and that comforted their raid mates. And to Kellory that came by to aid in the efforts. <br>
<br>
It was an experience that will allow us to grow and be stronger next time.  *chuckle* Just the taste of revenge should be enough to keep us all going <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <br>
<br>
As for me, I am hopeful that my loot master duties will be utilized on the next raid <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    *smile*<br>
<br>
