</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udesirrae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Desirrae</A> at: 8/23/01 2:10:08 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Unguilded Sexless Drood</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/23/01 12:18:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CoG down, but we'll be back with a vengence, Voxy!</span><hr size=1> Aye, I came in just in time to watch you guys hit Vox.  Sorry I couldnt come by earlier, but Wednesdays are a dinner night at my friends and so I got back late.  Mariners were kicking ass.<br>
<br>
One thing I would suggest is having a secondary commander that is a healer or caster.  I know Kommisar was taken down fairly early.  The thing is, about 2/3rds of the way through I was seeing shouts that most if not all the tanks were down.  The raid should have been called off at that point if true.  And I believe it was because soon after Vox made an appearence in the triage line.  She cannot be allowed in there.  If she appears in the triage line then people will get caught up in a death loop.  Indeed this is partially what happened later in the night.  Had the raid been called earlier, with fewer deaths, it might have been possible to rez the tanks and try again.  Casters alone cannot generally take Vox down.  You need tanks to keep her against the wall and to stun her.<br>
<br>
Now one thing I did see.  There is absolutely no reason or excuse to ever take out your fustrations on a GM or Guide.  There isnt anything any of them can do in a situation like ours and it was good of them just to show up and take a look.  Taking your fustrations out on them can cause them to not show up in a timely fashion later when we do need them.  They are bound by rules that we all agreed to when we clicked the I Agree button.  All I can say is the person who was involved in this is lucky I wasnt leading the raid otherwise you would've been kicked out of the raid and left to get a rez on your own.  I understand how tempers were flying at 2am with the servers coming down in an hour, but that is still no reason to lose it.  Especially to a member of the CSR staff.  Their lives are hard enough as it is, and there is no need for us to make it worse.<br>
<br>
