Master Forager<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Unguilded Sexless Drood</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/23/01 3:48:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CoG down, but we'll be back with a vengence, Voxy!</span><hr size=1> I suppose someone petitioned the GM's due to both the number of corpses, and because of some mobs camping bind points.  Other than possibly moving your bind point, theres not much a GM will do.  They did rez's and moved corpses for the Naggy raid due to the zone crashing.  We just failed.<br>
<br>
Yes, the triage line is over by the ramp because through the door is Vox.  This is generally a &quot;safe&quot; area since generally Vox does not leave her lair.  In fact, offically she actually cant due to her size.  I think last night's raid proved that is false tho.  heh.<br>
<br>
The reason behind all the healers helping to heal everyone is that we simply dont have enough clerics to go around.  These tanks can have upwards of 3k hps and gheal just doesnt cut it.  Especially when you consider your 51+ druids with supheal are actually inside nuking instead of healing.  It becomes a catch as catch can.  A few overlapped gheals wont make too much a difference.  Also with /serverfilter on it can take up to 6 seconds for you to see the results of someone else's heal on a tank's health bar.  That can mean the difference between a tank who can head back in to push Vox back and a dead tank.  I see it kind of like when your in a group and the enchanter gets hit.  I automaticly drop a supheal on the enchanter.  I know the cleric is also hitting them with a heal, but I'm not going to wait just in case they fizzle or the enchanter is taking more damage.  When healing someone that is essential to the success of the raid or group I dont see a couple of redundant heals as being bad.  Casters are nice, but on a Vox raid live tanks are simply essential.  Dead casters just mem new spells and run in again.  Dead tanks equal a dead raid.<br>
<br>
As for resists.  Common wisdom is that no, a healer's resists are not that important.  However, it IS possible for vox to fear you even in the triage line and if she is close enough to the door you become vulnerable to her regular cold AE.<br>
<br>
Now that being said, if you have enough tanks I think mana is more valuable than resists for the healers.  Especially when heals are not line of sight and nothing obstructs them, whereas AE's are and in general the walls of her lair will stop Vox's AE.  Of course, this is a tradeoff.  When you run OOM it is expected that you will immediatly run into the lair and get killed by Vox, respawn at the triage line, mem a heal, and keep going.  You might have to do this several times.  I think my personal record was 7, considerably more than when I was part of the nukers.  But.  If due to warping or healing aggro Vox gets too close to the triage line, you will need every one of those buffs.  A fear'd healer is a worthless healer same as a fear'd tank is useless.  Worse, the ramp area is lousy with pit traps and you can easily find yourself fear'd into one of them if you are unlucky.<br>
<br>
Also to consider, wis equals more mana only at the higher levels.  Indeed at 50 one point of wis is roughly equal to 10mana.  So if you sacrafice 30 wis (high but not unheard of) thats still only 300 mana at level 50, less if you are below that.  Thats like 2 gheals.  Probably not as significant as being fear'd once into a pit trap.<br>
<br>
That being said I think the healers can get away with only about a 50 or so resist to magic and cold unbuffed.  While ssome would argue being fear'd or oom its all the same, I'd point out you can suicide if oom, you cant if your fear'd.<br>
<br>
But thats just my take on resists.  My gut feeling is this game post 50 is all about AC and resists.  Everything else is secondary.  Doesnt matter what class you are.<br>
<br>
